                  ) that comes out of our own bellies, being miſtaken for the ſtill language, in which God was once heard, a congregation of Chriſtians may be ſoon inſpired into a legion of Demoniacks, and onely one (but that a teeming fruitful) error be committed all this while, the miſtaking our own motions for the incitation of the Spirit of God, which till it be reformed or retracted, it muſt be a ſhortneſs of diſcourſe to think ſtrange, and an injuſtice to charge of any new crime, the infallible conſequences of it, and ſuch are all the barefaced villanies in the world.
